For my project, I used Canva, an online graphic design tool, to create a visually appealing and well-structured design. Canva provided a variety of templates, icons, and customization options that made it easy to organize my ideas and present them clearly. My design focuses on presenting the main concept of the topic through a combination of text, images, and color themes, making it both informative and engaging for the viewer.

The design shows a clear layout with headings, subheadings, and relevant visuals that help in better understanding of the content. I used contrasting colors and simple fonts to maintain readability while also ensuring that the design looks attractive. The visuals included icons and illustrations that support the information and make the overall presentation more interactive.

One thing I found interesting while making this design was exploring different layout styles and color combinations to see what works best. However, I also found it slightly difficult to balance creativity with simplicity, as adding too many elements can make the design look cluttered. Overall, it was a valuable learning experience.
